{
  "texts": [
    "The good regime, where the structural function aligns strongly with the leading eigenspaces of the conditional expectation operator T, and the singular values of T decay slowly; 2.",
    "The bad regime, where spectral alignment holds, but rapid singular value decay leads to instability and degraded estimation quality; 3.",
    "The ugly regime, where the structural function is misaligned with the top eigenspaces of T, rendering spectral methods ineffective regardless of decay rate.",
    "Overview of contributions.",
    "We investigate the effectiveness of spectral features in NPIV estimation, grounding their empirical success in a principled theoretical analysis."
  ]
}